docs.abstract: The Federal Reserve is primarily watching progress on inflation as it contemplates its next steps, but it is also keeping an eye on the labor market.
docs.snippet: The Federal Reserve is primarily watching progress on inflation as it contemplates its next steps, but it is also keeping an eye on the labor market.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve is considering when and how much to cut interest rates, and the employment report on Friday will give policymakers an up-to-date hint at how the economy is evolving ahead of their next policy meeting.

headline.main: The jobs report comes as the Fed considers the timing of interest rate cuts.

docs.abstract: The president used his State of the Union speech to pitch tax increases for the rich, along with plans to cut costs and protect consumers.
docs.snippet: The president used his State of the Union speech to pitch tax increases for the rich, along with plans to cut costs and protect consumers.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Biden used his State of the Union speech on Thursday to remind Americans of his efforts to steer the nation’s economy out of a pandemic recession, and to lay the groundwork for a second term focused on making the economy more equitable by raising taxes on companies and the wealthy while taking steps to reduce costs for the middle class.

headline.main: Biden Portrays Next Phase of Economic Agenda as Middle-Class Lifeline

docs.abstract: Economists are trying to gauge whether forecasts of a slowing labor market were mistaken or just premature. For now, gains are consistent and strong.
docs.snippet: Economists are trying to gauge whether forecasts of a slowing labor market were mistaken or just premature. For now, gains are consistent and strong.
docs.lead_paragraph: If the economy is slowing down, nobody told the labor market.

headline.main: U.S. Employers Add 275,000 Jobs in Another Strong Month
headline.print_headline: Hiring Trend Stays Strong As U.S. Adds 275,000 Jobs

docs.abstract: Tech layoffs, fallout from Hollywood strikes and an uptick in rural joblessness challenge a state with one of the nation’s highest unemployment rates.
docs.snippet: Tech layoffs, fallout from Hollywood strikes and an uptick in rural joblessness challenge a state with one of the nation’s highest unemployment rates.
docs.lead_paragraph: For decades, California’s behemoth economy has outpaced those of most nations, holding an outsize role in shaping global trends in tech, entertainment and agriculture.

headline.main: Unemployment Casts a Shadow Over California’s Economy

docs.abstract: Immigrants aided the pandemic recovery and may be crucial to future needs. The challenge is processing newcomers and getting them where the jobs are.
docs.snippet: Immigrants aided the pandemic recovery and may be crucial to future needs. The challenge is processing newcomers and getting them where the jobs are.
docs.lead_paragraph: The U.S. economic recovery from the pandemic has been stronger and more durable than many experts had expected, and a rebound in immigration is a big reason.

headline.main: The U.S. Economy Is Surpassing Expectations. Immigration Is One Reason.
headline.print_headline: Migrants, Ready to Work, Face Many Roadblocks

docs.abstract: Meet the 1990 and 1991 babies, a massive microgeneration in lifelong competition for America’s economic resources, reshaping the world around them.
docs.snippet: Meet the 1990 and 1991 babies, a massive microgeneration in lifelong competition for America’s economic resources, reshaping the world around them.
docs.lead_paragraph: I have covered economics for 11 years now, and in that time, I have come to the realization that I am a statistic. Every time I make a major life choice, I promptly watch it become the thing that everyone is doing that year.

headline.main: It’s Me, Hi, I’m the Problem. I’m 33.
headline.print_headline: Life at the Crest of a Demographic Tsunami

docs.abstract: The president and his team are seeking ways to help Americans afford to rent and buy homes, as high borrowing costs dampen views of the economy.
docs.snippet: The president and his team are seeking ways to help Americans afford to rent and buy homes, as high borrowing costs dampen views of the economy.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Biden and his economic team, concerned that elevated mortgage rates and housing costs are hurting Americans and hindering his re-election bid, are searching for new ways to make housing more available and affordable.

headline.main: High Mortgage Rates Leave Biden Searching for Housing Relief
headline.print_headline: Housing Crunch Could Hinder Biden’s 2024 Bid

docs.abstract: Have you noticed your grocery products shrinking? Here’s how that gets counted — and what gets missed — in inflation data.
docs.snippet: Have you noticed your grocery products shrinking? Here’s how that gets counted — and what gets missed — in inflation data.
docs.lead_paragraph: Grocery store shoppers are noticing something amiss. Air-filled bags of chips. Shrunken soup cans. Diminished detergent packages.

headline.main: Shrinkflation 101: The Economics of Smaller Groceries
headline.print_headline: Large Impact Of Incredible Shrinking Groceries

docs.abstract: Costlier vehicles and repairs are pushing premiums higher even as the increase in U.S. consumer prices is tapering overall.
docs.snippet: Costlier vehicles and repairs are pushing premiums higher even as the increase in U.S. consumer prices is tapering overall.
docs.lead_paragraph: Job growth, wage growth and business growth are all lively, and inflation has steeply fallen from its 2022 highs. But consumer sentiment, while improving, is still sour.

headline.main: Auto Insurance Spike Hampers the Inflation Fight
headline.print_headline: The Effect of Inflation Is Still Felt in Surging Car Insurance Rates

docs.abstract: The Treasury secretary said she called on Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel to reduce barriers to commerce for Palestinians.
docs.snippet: The Treasury secretary said she called on Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel to reduce barriers to commerce for Palestinians.
docs.lead_paragraph: Treasury Secretary Janet L. Yellen said on Tuesday that she had personally urged Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel to increase commercial engagement with the West Bank, contending that doing so was important for the economic welfare of both Israelis and Palestinians.

headline.main: Yellen Urges Israel to Restore Economic Ties to West Bank
headline.print_headline: Yellen Urges Netanyahu to Restore Israel’s Economic Ties to the West Bank
